And the ones that
are mentioned here

00:42:53.260 --> 00:42:55.640 align:middle line:84%
are attachment, aversion,
and indifference,

00:42:55.640 --> 00:42:58.870 align:middle line:84%
which is also attraction and
repulsion and essentially

00:42:58.870 --> 00:42:59.870 align:middle line:90%
indifference, right?

00:42:59.870 --> 00:43:00.670 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Yeah.

00:43:00.670 --> 00:43:03.277 align:middle line:84%
And so that's really the flow
of energy through our egos.

00:43:03.277 --> 00:43:04.860 align:middle line:84%
It's just really our
ego conditioning.

00:43:04.860 --> 00:43:06.901 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's really
where a lot of people

00:43:06.901 --> 00:43:09.650 align:middle line:84%
get hung up, so
let's talk about it.

00:43:09.650 --> 00:43:12.990 align:middle line:84%
Life, all of life, is based
on attraction and repulsion.

00:43:12.990 --> 00:43:15.430 align:middle line:84%
That's the nature of
the universe itself.

00:43:15.430 --> 00:43:17.032 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Well, it can be, sure.

00:43:17.032 --> 00:43:18.490 align:middle line:84%
That is the nature
of the universe.

00:43:18.490 --> 00:43:19.969 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Just on
an atomic level.

00:43:19.969 --> 00:43:21.010 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Yes, that's true.

00:43:21.010 --> 00:43:22.830 align:middle line:84%
It's the law of
cause and effect.

00:43:22.830 --> 00:43:26.140 align:middle line:84%
That's the duality that
we live in, absolutely.

00:43:26.140 --> 00:43:29.350 align:middle line:84%
And I think the skill that
a lot of these religious and

00:43:29.350 --> 00:43:31.120 align:middle line:84%
spiritual traditions
are trying to help us

00:43:31.120 --> 00:43:33.610 align:middle line:84%
with is the ability
to observe that

00:43:33.610 --> 00:43:35.440 align:middle line:90%
without getting caught into it.

00:43:35.440 --> 00:43:37.510 align:middle line:90%
So we're human beings.

00:43:37.510 --> 00:43:39.010 align:middle line:90%
We want for things.

00:43:39.010 --> 00:43:40.826 align:middle line:90%
We avoid certain things.

00:43:40.826 --> 00:43:42.700 align:middle line:84%
But is there a way that
we can lean into that

00:43:42.700 --> 00:43:45.970 align:middle line:84%
and actually observe
that wanting, observe

00:43:45.970 --> 00:43:49.420 align:middle line:84%
that repulsion in a way that
we're not consumed by it?

00:43:49.420 --> 00:43:51.190 align:middle line:84%
Because it's when we
get consumed by it

00:43:51.190 --> 00:43:53.090 align:middle line:90%
that we run into problems.

00:43:53.090 --> 00:43:54.790 align:middle line:84%
It's when I'm so
attached to something

00:43:54.790 --> 00:43:57.490 align:middle line:84%
that I can't see
everything else around me.

00:43:57.490 --> 00:44:00.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Either way creates a
lot of resistance in our lives.

00:44:00.400 --> 00:44:03.130 align:middle line:84%
Whether something is being
taken away or foisted upon us,

00:44:03.130 --> 00:44:07.300 align:middle line:84%
there's resistance either way
if we have too strong a vantage

00:44:07.300 --> 00:44:08.870 align:middle line:90%
point or a viewpoint, right?

00:44:08.870 --> 00:44:09.670 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Absolutely.

00:44:09.670 --> 00:44:12.970 align:middle line:84%
And essentially, what that does
is those strong attachments

00:44:12.970 --> 00:44:15.680 align:middle line:84%
and aversions create
karma-- again,

00:44:15.680 --> 00:44:17.700 align:middle line:84%
going back to that
karmic sheath,

00:44:17.700 --> 00:44:20.020 align:middle line:84%
you're literally creating
more subtle matter that

00:44:20.020 --> 00:44:22.450 align:middle line:90%
obscures the light of the soul.

00:44:22.450 --> 00:44:26.140 align:middle line:84%
So yes, attachment and
aversion are part of life.

00:44:26.140 --> 00:44:27.400 align:middle line:90%
But the trick is--

00:44:27.400 --> 00:44:28.420 align:middle line:90%
there's a trick.

00:44:28.420 --> 00:44:31.600 align:middle line:84%
The trick is really to
watch it so that you're not

00:44:31.600 --> 00:44:33.190 align:middle line:84%
attached to your
attachment, you're

00:44:33.190 --> 00:44:35.140 align:middle line:90%
not attached to your aversion.

00:44:35.140 --> 00:44:36.880 align:middle line:90%
Does that make sense?

00:44:36.880 --> 00:44:39.880 align:middle line:84%
So then the light of the soul
is able to shine through more

00:44:39.880 --> 00:44:42.340 align:middle line:84%
clearly and guide you
on your purpose in life.

00:44:42.340 --> 00:44:45.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It seems to me
actually quite simple in that

00:44:45.280 --> 00:44:48.150 align:middle line:84%
if you are able to listen
to these subtle feelings--

00:44:48.150 --> 00:44:50.680 align:middle line:84%
as I call them, the
whisperings of the soul--

00:44:50.680 --> 00:44:53.980 align:middle line:84%
that you tread through
life a little more lightly.

00:44:53.980 --> 00:44:57.580 align:middle line:84%
And you allow yourself, whether
it's your preference or not

00:44:57.580 --> 00:44:59.620 align:middle line:84%
in the moment, to
be guided where

00:44:59.620 --> 00:45:00.940 align:middle line:90%
you need to go in that moment.

00:45:00.940 --> 00:45:02.960 align:middle line:84%
And that is where
a lot of people,

00:45:02.960 --> 00:45:07.450 align:middle line:84%
especially in a very
willful world, get hung up.

00:45:07.450 --> 00:45:10.480 align:middle line:84%
Once a desire is created
for a specific outcome,

00:45:10.480 --> 00:45:11.945 align:middle line:90%
then comes the attachment.

00:45:11.945 --> 00:45:13.570 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes we're
doing it because we

00:45:13.570 --> 00:45:18.550 align:middle line:84%
think we're supposed to, because
there's some societal pressure

00:45:18.550 --> 00:45:19.350 align:middle line:90%
to do it.

00:45:19.350 --> 00:45:21.370 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter if
it's driven by that

00:45:21.370 --> 00:45:25.090 align:middle line:84%
or just garden variety
attractions and repulsions.

00:45:25.090 --> 00:45:32.260 align:middle line:84%
But to me, if you can't just
listen and respond accordingly,

00:45:32.260 --> 00:45:35.200 align:middle line:84%
life becomes nothing
but resistance.

00:45:35.200 --> 00:45:41.200 align:middle line:84%
So how can you avoid building
up more of this subtle matter

00:45:41.200 --> 00:45:42.170 align:middle line:90%
called karma?

00:45:42.170 --> 00:45:42.970 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Yeah.

00:45:42.970 --> 00:45:46.360 align:middle line:84%
I think a key thing is really
widening our perspectives.

00:45:46.360 --> 00:45:48.920 align:middle line:84%
We live in an increasingly
self-referential world.

00:45:48.920 --> 00:45:50.110 align:middle line:90%
We have our social media.

00:45:50.110 --> 00:45:51.597 align:middle line:90%
We have all of these things.

00:45:51.597 --> 00:45:53.680 align:middle line:84%
And now we get self-referential
about our purpose.

00:45:53.680 --> 00:45:54.929 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my god, what's my purpose?

00:45:54.929 --> 00:45:57.100 align:middle line:90%
What's my purpose?

00:45:57.100 --> 00:46:00.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's really
getting boring.

00:46:00.080 --> 00:46:01.780 align:middle line:84%
>>JAIN: Yeah, it can
get really boring,

00:46:01.780 --> 00:46:04.780 align:middle line:90%
because it's lonely too.

00:46:04.780 --> 00:46:07.540 align:middle line:84%
So when we widen our
perspective while doing

00:46:07.540 --> 00:46:09.070 align:middle line:84%
these kinds of
spiritual practices

00:46:09.070 --> 00:46:12.700 align:middle line:84%
that connect us both to
spirit and with each other,

00:46:12.700 --> 00:46:14.260 align:middle line:90%
we widen our lens.

00:46:14.260 --> 00:46:15.880 align:middle line:84%
We don't take
things as seriously.

00:46:15.880 --> 00:46:18.740 align:middle line:84%
We're able to watch and
observe, and like you said,

00:46:18.740 --> 00:46:23.320 align:middle line:84%
be light with the process,
have fun with the process,

00:46:23.320 --> 00:46:25.720 align:middle line:90%
and let go of our rigidity.

00:46:25.720 --> 00:46:27.310 align:middle line:90%
That's really important.

00:46:27.310 --> 00:46:31.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: One time a being that
I'm closely associated with

00:46:31.630 --> 00:46:34.010 align:middle line:84%
that I chat with
from time to time--

00:46:34.010 --> 00:46:37.420 align:middle line:84%
the being was saying that
the conscious mind as we

00:46:37.420 --> 00:46:39.680 align:middle line:84%
know it, the animal portion
of the conscious mind,

00:46:39.680 --> 00:46:43.300 align:middle line:84%
they say it was initially
only there to keep you

00:46:43.300 --> 00:46:46.210 align:middle line:90%
from bumping into things.

00:46:46.210 --> 00:46:50.260 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't the part that
was taken over, dominated,

00:46:50.260 --> 00:46:54.070 align:middle line:84%
making your life decisions
for you now to the point where

00:46:54.070 --> 00:46:56.590 align:middle line:84%
essentially, you can't even
hear the real mind, which

00:46:56.590 --> 00:46:58.450 align:middle line:90%
is the whispering of the soul.

00:46:58.450 --> 00:47:02.860 align:middle line:84%
And so I assume that part of
the practice, the practice

00:47:02.860 --> 00:47:06.010 align:middle line:84%
element of the
Jan tradition, has

00:47:06.010 --> 00:47:09.280 align:middle line:84%
to be removing the
noise so that you

00:47:09.280 --> 00:47:14.170 align:middle line:84%
can hear the soul or the higher
mind speak through to you.

00:47:14.170 --> 00:47:15.020 align:middle line:90%
Is that correct?

00:47:15.020 --> 00:47:15.610 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Absolutely, yeah.

00:47:15.610 --> 00:47:18.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then get this
lower mind that's chatting

00:47:18.100 --> 00:47:20.280 align:middle line:84%
away, telling us what we
should and shouldn't do,

00:47:20.280 --> 00:47:22.760 align:middle line:84%
and holds shame-- that's
subconscious-- but nonetheless,

00:47:22.760 --> 00:47:24.740 align:middle line:90%
all of this baggage with it--

00:47:24.740 --> 00:47:27.910 align:middle line:84%
it really has to
take a backseat.

00:47:27.910 --> 00:47:30.190 align:middle line:84%
That is what's causing
the problem in us.

00:47:30.190 --> 00:47:31.750 align:middle line:84%
And yet we all have
to deal with it.

00:47:31.750 --> 00:47:33.586 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Yeah, it's really true.

00:47:33.586 --> 00:47:35.710 align:middle line:84%
And these tried and true
spiritual practices really

00:47:35.710 --> 00:47:38.370 align:middle line:84%
help us to filter
out that mind noise

00:47:38.370 --> 00:47:42.730 align:middle line:84%
to clarify a direct channel
with our spirit guides,

00:47:42.730 --> 00:47:44.230 align:middle line:90%
with our souls.

00:47:44.230 --> 00:47:46.060 align:middle line:84%
And so in the Jan
tradition, that's

00:47:46.060 --> 00:47:49.130 align:middle line:84%
generally taken in the
form of mantra meditations.

00:47:49.130 --> 00:47:51.100 align:middle line:84%
So we have a lot
of mantric prayers

00:47:51.100 --> 00:47:54.400 align:middle line:84%
that we do that help to
stabilize the energy field.

00:47:54.400 --> 00:47:56.440 align:middle line:84%
There are color
meditations as well

00:47:56.440 --> 00:48:02.290 align:middle line:84%
to bring in color into the
body, again with verbalizations

00:48:02.290 --> 00:48:04.750 align:middle line:90%
of mantras to do that.

00:48:04.750 --> 00:48:06.850 align:middle line:84%
So there's definitely
that tradition,

00:48:06.850 --> 00:48:08.410 align:middle line:84%
very similar to
Vedic traditions,

00:48:08.410 --> 00:48:10.390 align:middle line:84%
the traditions of really
getting into the body

00:48:10.390 --> 00:48:12.760 align:middle line:84%
and relaxing every
single part of the body.

00:48:12.760 --> 00:48:14.800 align:middle line:84%
Because we understand
that all the impulses that

00:48:14.800 --> 00:48:18.730 align:middle line:84%
are going on here are
mental emotional, basically.

00:48:18.730 --> 00:48:21.370 align:middle line:84%
Everything that's happening
is here reflected in the body.

00:48:21.370 --> 00:48:23.800 align:middle line:84%
And so by getting
the body quiet,

00:48:23.800 --> 00:48:26.890 align:middle line:84%
we help get the mind quiet,
and we allow for spirit

00:48:26.890 --> 00:48:29.480 align:middle line:84%
to come more fully
present in our bodies.

00:48:29.480 --> 00:48:31.120 align:middle line:90%
And these are universal.

00:48:31.120 --> 00:48:34.650 align:middle line:84%
I just had the beauty of
sitting with a Chilean healer.

00:48:34.650 --> 00:48:35.780 align:middle line:90%
It was just amazing.

00:48:35.780 --> 00:48:37.150 align:middle line:90%
It was this past week.

00:48:37.150 --> 00:48:38.830 align:middle line:84%
And there's so many
similarities in all

00:48:38.830 --> 00:48:42.370 align:middle line:84%
of these indigenous approaches
and Christian approaches,

00:48:42.370 --> 00:48:44.830 align:middle line:90%
all of these different--

00:48:44.830 --> 00:48:47.830 align:middle line:84%
Judaism, even, I would
say to a degree, probably

00:48:47.830 --> 00:48:50.600 align:middle line:90%
Islam and others--

00:48:50.600 --> 00:48:54.520 align:middle line:84%
there's always a reminder to
refocus back on sensation,

00:48:54.520 --> 00:48:56.270 align:middle line:90%
to anchor back into the body.

00:48:56.270 --> 00:48:58.990 align:middle line:84%
And so as we start doing
that, for if we're just

00:48:58.990 --> 00:49:01.570 align:middle line:84%
learning about it, we start
feeling the sensations

00:49:01.570 --> 00:49:03.160 align:middle line:90%
associated with our emotions.

00:49:03.160 --> 00:49:05.410 align:middle line:84%
And then we start learning
about the thoughts that are

00:49:05.410 --> 00:49:06.701 align:middle line:90%
associated with those emotions.

00:49:06.701 --> 00:49:10.400 align:middle line:84%
And then once we've
cleared the bubbling river,

00:49:10.400 --> 00:49:13.630 align:middle line:84%
and we're getting more
to lake level, stillness

00:49:13.630 --> 00:49:16.290 align:middle line:84%
of the ripples of
sensation in our body,

00:49:16.290 --> 00:49:18.430 align:middle line:84%
then we get into the
more subtle aspects.

00:49:18.430 --> 00:49:23.320 align:middle line:84%
And the subtle sensations
give us spiritual messages.

00:49:23.320 --> 00:49:25.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So once
we begin to quiet it

00:49:25.600 --> 00:49:28.890 align:middle line:84%
all down so we can
actually listen,

00:49:28.890 --> 00:49:32.690 align:middle line:84%
one of the things that
pops up is trauma.

00:49:32.690 --> 00:49:35.740 align:middle line:84%
And we have to somehow
interface with that trauma.

00:49:35.740 --> 00:49:38.230 align:middle line:10%
And this is something
in Tiffany's work,

00:49:38.230 --> 00:49:40.060 align:middle line:10%
Eileen McKusick's work.

00:49:40.060 --> 00:49:42.970 align:middle line:10%
When she's using
her tuning processes

00:49:42.970 --> 00:49:45.210 align:middle line:10%
to go through the subtle
layers of our history,

00:49:45.210 --> 00:49:48.130 align:middle line:10%
you keep hitting trauma,
disturbances in the field,

00:49:48.130 --> 00:49:49.510 align:middle line:10%
another disturbance
in the field.

00:49:49.510 --> 00:49:51.490 align:middle line:10%
And then on the other
side of the body,

00:49:51.490 --> 00:49:54.700 align:middle line:10%
she looks at how this is
expressed out in our behavior

00:49:54.700 --> 00:49:56.850 align:middle line:10%
at this point in time
and into the future.

00:49:56.850 --> 00:49:58.210 align:middle line:90%
It's fascinating.

00:49:58.210 --> 00:50:00.340 align:middle line:84%
So looking at it from
that point of view,

00:50:00.340 --> 00:50:03.140 align:middle line:90%
how is trauma worked with?

00:50:03.140 --> 00:50:04.630 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Yeah.

00:50:04.630 --> 00:50:07.360 align:middle line:84%
It's very similar to these
other healing approaches

00:50:07.360 --> 00:50:10.600 align:middle line:84%
in that as you clarify
the light of the soul,

00:50:10.600 --> 00:50:13.810 align:middle line:84%
you gain the power to release
those karmic patterns that

00:50:13.810 --> 00:50:19.280 align:middle line:84%
stay in the biofield and keep
that trauma pattern running.

00:50:19.280 --> 00:50:22.810 align:middle line:84%
So if there is a karmic
trace of that trauma, which

00:50:22.810 --> 00:50:23.620 align:middle line:90%
often there is--

00:50:23.620 --> 00:50:24.600 align:middle line:90%
trauma runs deep.

00:50:24.600 --> 00:50:27.910 align:middle line:84%
It's usually felt
on a karmic level.

00:50:27.910 --> 00:50:31.330 align:middle line:84%
As we go through the processes
of spiritual awakening,

00:50:31.330 --> 00:50:33.760 align:middle line:84%
spiritual liberation,
a lot of those traumas

00:50:33.760 --> 00:50:35.170 align:middle line:84%
will come to light
when they seek

00:50:35.170 --> 00:50:39.014 align:middle line:84%
help with them, like going
to a healer, for example,

00:50:39.014 --> 00:50:40.555 align:middle line:84%
or going to a
spiritual practitioner,

00:50:40.555 --> 00:50:43.105 align:middle line:84%
or going to friends,
sharing what's

00:50:43.105 --> 00:50:44.230 align:middle line:90%
coming up for me right now.

00:50:44.230 --> 00:50:45.438 align:middle line:90%
It could be past life trauma.

00:50:45.438 --> 00:50:48.160 align:middle line:84%
It could be a lot
of different things.

00:50:48.160 --> 00:50:50.110 align:middle line:84%
By clarifying the
light of the soul,

00:50:50.110 --> 00:50:51.850 align:middle line:84%
we're able to release
those patterns.

00:50:51.850 --> 00:50:54.610 align:middle line:84%
And once we release those
patterns on the karmic level,

00:50:54.610 --> 00:50:58.210 align:middle line:84%
they no longer plague
our mind and our emotions

00:50:58.210 --> 00:51:01.520 align:middle line:84%
and our behaviors in the
way that they had before.

00:51:01.520 --> 00:51:04.140 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes, as you know,
when you do deep work,

00:51:04.140 --> 00:51:05.890 align:middle line:84%
you don't even know
it's going to come up.

00:51:05.890 --> 00:51:07.431 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
there's a trauma

00:51:07.431 --> 00:51:10.300 align:middle line:84%
that comes up that you
weren't even aware of before.

00:51:10.300 --> 00:51:11.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, absolutely.

00:51:11.680 --> 00:51:13.200 align:middle line:90%
And it can come up in layers.

00:51:13.200 --> 00:51:17.980 align:middle line:84%
And so when I think of the
trauma that's carried forward

00:51:17.980 --> 00:51:22.180 align:middle line:84%
in this lifetime and from other
lifetimes, in my vernacular,

00:51:22.180 --> 00:51:25.060 align:middle line:84%
that would be contained within
what we call the subconscious.

00:51:25.060 --> 00:51:29.500 align:middle line:84%
So how does the word
"karma" and this karmic body

00:51:29.500 --> 00:51:33.820 align:middle line:84%
interface with the notion,
or maybe the Western notion,

00:51:33.820 --> 00:51:35.090 align:middle line:90%
of the subconscious mind?

00:51:35.090 --> 00:51:35.890 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Yeah.

00:51:35.890 --> 00:51:38.390 align:middle line:84%
Well, recall that we talked
about these emanations

00:51:38.390 --> 00:51:39.190 align:middle line:90%
of karma.

00:51:39.190 --> 00:51:42.680 align:middle line:84%
In the Jan tradition, they
describe them as twofold.

00:51:42.680 --> 00:51:45.640 align:middle line:84%
One is psychical, meaning
the mind and emotions,

00:51:45.640 --> 00:51:47.270 align:middle line:90%
and one is physical.

00:51:47.270 --> 00:51:50.470 align:middle line:84%
So we can see how the
emanations of consciousness

00:51:50.470 --> 00:51:54.280 align:middle line:84%
and our conscious experience get
lodged into our bodies as well

00:51:54.280 --> 00:51:55.930 align:middle line:90%
as our mind and emotions.

00:51:55.930 --> 00:51:59.830 align:middle line:84%
So that is the adivasi,
or the karmic emanations

00:51:59.830 --> 00:52:01.390 align:middle line:90%
that spring forth.

00:52:01.390 --> 00:52:03.490 align:middle line:90%
Those are not always conscious.

00:52:03.490 --> 00:52:04.600 align:middle line:90%
But what I've noticed--

00:52:04.600 --> 00:52:07.480 align:middle line:84%
and likely, I think, all
healers and practitioners

00:52:07.480 --> 00:52:09.880 align:middle line:84%
have noticed-- is
that even when they're

00:52:09.880 --> 00:52:12.760 align:middle line:84%
lodged in the subconscious, they
play a role in our behavior.

00:52:12.760 --> 00:52:13.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:52:13.870 --> 00:52:15.730 align:middle line:84%
They're driving
behavior unconsciously.

00:52:15.730 --> 00:52:16.530 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Absolutely.

00:52:16.530 --> 00:52:18.490 align:middle line:84%
So we just simply start
looking at our behavior

00:52:18.490 --> 00:52:20.640 align:middle line:84%
patterns, especially the things
that aren't working for us

00:52:20.640 --> 00:52:22.723 align:middle line:84%
and things that are causing
us pain and suffering,

00:52:22.723 --> 00:52:24.820 align:middle line:84%
and we say what
is going on here.

00:52:24.820 --> 00:52:28.840 align:middle line:84%
Why is this pattern continuing
to come forth in my life?

00:52:28.840 --> 00:52:30.790 align:middle line:84%
And how can I look
deeply into that?

00:52:30.790 --> 00:52:32.830 align:middle line:84%
And maybe we don't
know the origin of it.

00:52:32.830 --> 00:52:34.240 align:middle line:84%
There are some
healers, including

00:52:34.240 --> 00:52:37.874 align:middle line:84%
Rosalyn, who believe that you
don't have to know everything

00:52:37.874 --> 00:52:39.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what I
was going to ask next.

00:52:39.790 --> 00:52:40.590 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:52:40.590 --> 00:52:43.160 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about that--
we have a little bit of time

00:52:43.160 --> 00:52:43.960 align:middle line:90%
here--

00:52:43.960 --> 00:52:46.250 align:middle line:84%
about the two different
schools of thought.

00:52:46.250 --> 00:52:47.170 align:middle line:90%
You have to get to it.

00:52:47.170 --> 00:52:48.130 align:middle line:90%
You have to relive it.

00:52:48.130 --> 00:52:50.050 align:middle line:84%
You get in the pain,
and boom, that's

00:52:50.050 --> 00:52:52.240 align:middle line:84%
going to somehow
disperse it, right?

00:52:52.240 --> 00:52:53.400 align:middle line:90%
Not necessarily.

00:52:53.400 --> 00:52:54.200 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: No.

00:52:54.200 --> 00:52:56.620 align:middle line:84%
In fact, there is an
understanding among many of us

00:52:56.620 --> 00:52:59.050 align:middle line:90%
that if a healer--

00:52:59.050 --> 00:53:03.390 align:middle line:84%
let's say if a healer does not
know how to skillfully remove

00:53:03.390 --> 00:53:05.710 align:middle line:84%
a trauma at the
karmic level, they

00:53:05.710 --> 00:53:07.360 align:middle line:90%
may actually just basically--

00:53:07.360 --> 00:53:08.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Re-traumatized.

00:53:08.510 --> 00:53:12.160 align:middle line:84%
>>JAIN: Yeah, you just amplified
the traumatic pattern, which

00:53:12.160 --> 00:53:14.590 align:middle line:84%
might serve if someone
really needs to wake up

00:53:14.590 --> 00:53:16.600 align:middle line:84%
to their traumatic
pattern, but it may cause

00:53:16.600 --> 00:53:18.550 align:middle line:90%
a lot of suffering as well.

00:53:18.550 --> 00:53:20.500 align:middle line:90%
So I personally think--

00:53:20.500 --> 00:53:23.514 align:middle line:90%
this is on a case-by-case basis.

00:53:23.514 --> 00:53:25.180 align:middle line:84%
For me, one of the
most important things

00:53:25.180 --> 00:53:26.805 align:middle line:84%
that I've learned
personally in working

00:53:26.805 --> 00:53:29.500 align:middle line:84%
with trauma with patients
with PTSD and others

00:53:29.500 --> 00:53:31.870 align:middle line:90%
is that you create a container.

00:53:31.870 --> 00:53:34.280 align:middle line:84%
Creating a container for
me has worked really well.

00:53:34.280 --> 00:53:37.030 align:middle line:84%
So you really create
a space of light

00:53:37.030 --> 00:53:39.820 align:middle line:84%
that allows that karmic
trace to release.

00:53:39.820 --> 00:53:43.220 align:middle line:84%
And those of us who have helped
people release their trauma

00:53:43.220 --> 00:53:44.020 align:middle line:90%
have seen that.

00:53:44.020 --> 00:53:48.310 align:middle line:84%
There's a flash, and it comes
often with a flash of insight.

00:53:48.310 --> 00:53:50.800 align:middle line:84%
It comes with an energetic
feeling of something

00:53:50.800 --> 00:53:52.450 align:middle line:90%
leaving the body.

00:53:52.450 --> 00:53:54.877 align:middle line:84%
But if you're trying to
dig in there and get it--

00:53:54.877 --> 00:53:55.960 align:middle line:90%
it's kind of like you're--

00:53:55.960 --> 00:53:57.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Give it a
name, give it a face.

00:53:57.240 --> 00:53:57.850 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Yeah.

00:53:57.850 --> 00:54:00.340 align:middle line:84%
I don't know that it's always
so helpful, unless the person is

00:54:00.340 --> 00:54:02.470 align:middle line:84%
coming where they're present and
they need to talk it through.

00:54:02.470 --> 00:54:05.080 align:middle line:84%
And we see this a lot, even
in chronic pain-- for example,

00:54:05.080 --> 00:54:06.970 align:middle line:84%
a lot of work I've
done with veterans.

00:54:06.970 --> 00:54:08.800 align:middle line:84%
Of course they
always send veterans

00:54:08.800 --> 00:54:11.440 align:middle line:84%
to the psychologist when they're
using up too many services,

00:54:11.440 --> 00:54:13.794 align:middle line:84%
and they're trying to get
them to utilize less services,

00:54:13.794 --> 00:54:15.710 align:middle line:84%
so they send them to the
psychologist instead.

00:54:15.710 --> 00:54:17.350 align:middle line:84%
And you can see
how they're stuck

00:54:17.350 --> 00:54:20.290 align:middle line:84%
in their narrative of trauma
that's not necessarily

00:54:20.290 --> 00:54:22.520 align:middle line:90%
helping them move forward.

00:54:22.520 --> 00:54:26.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Are you able to, in
that practice with veterans,

00:54:26.100 --> 00:54:29.500 align:middle line:84%
utilize some of your more
ancient and mystical knowledge

00:54:29.500 --> 00:54:30.410 align:middle line:90%
to work with them?

00:54:30.410 --> 00:54:31.010 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Yeah, of course.

00:54:31.010 --> 00:54:32.801 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or do you
have to do it covertly?

00:54:32.801 --> 00:54:34.930 align:middle line:84%
>>JAIN: So I'll share with
you on a personal level,

00:54:34.930 --> 00:54:36.850 align:middle line:90%
I never sat for my licensure.

00:54:36.850 --> 00:54:39.280 align:middle line:84%
And I did that on
purpose-- because I

00:54:39.280 --> 00:54:41.940 align:middle line:84%
didn't want to be
constrained and feel

00:54:41.940 --> 00:54:44.080 align:middle line:84%
like, as a clinical
psychologist,

00:54:44.080 --> 00:54:45.610 align:middle line:90%
I'm not allowed to touch people.

00:54:45.610 --> 00:54:47.512 align:middle line:84%
And quite frankly, most
of my full-time work

00:54:47.512 --> 00:54:49.720 align:middle line:84%
is really being done in the
Consciousness and Healing

00:54:49.720 --> 00:54:51.820 align:middle line:90%
Initiative and directing that.

00:54:51.820 --> 00:54:57.430 align:middle line:84%
But when I work with someone who
has trauma like this, generally

00:54:57.430 --> 00:55:02.920 align:middle line:84%
speaking, it D depending
on what their openness is,

00:55:02.920 --> 00:55:04.260 align:middle line:90%
we may talk about it.

00:55:04.260 --> 00:55:06.880 align:middle line:84%
But it's, as you know,
kind of a felt thing.

00:55:06.880 --> 00:55:08.380 align:middle line:90%
Their guides come in.

00:55:08.380 --> 00:55:09.820 align:middle line:90%
My guides come in.

00:55:09.820 --> 00:55:13.400 align:middle line:84%
I may intend to just hold
them in a pillar of light.

00:55:13.400 --> 00:55:14.955 align:middle line:90%
And that has worked really well.

00:55:14.955 --> 00:55:17.080 align:middle line:10%
You think about-- I don't
want to digress too much,

00:55:17.080 --> 00:55:19.180 align:middle line:10%
but you think about
the work of Carl Rogers

00:55:19.180 --> 00:55:20.680 align:middle line:10%
and that famous,
famous session he

00:55:20.680 --> 00:55:24.940 align:middle line:10%
had where he sat in
silence with his patient,

00:55:24.940 --> 00:55:27.790 align:middle line:10%
and this patient had an
enormous breakthrough.

00:55:27.790 --> 00:55:29.050 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Oh, absolutely.

00:55:29.050 --> 00:55:31.860 align:middle line:84%
>>JAIN: And the psychologists
were like, what happened?

00:55:31.860 --> 00:55:33.880 align:middle line:84%
And the healers understand
it all too well.

00:55:33.880 --> 00:55:35.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
years ago, I used

00:55:35.290 --> 00:55:41.560 align:middle line:84%
to do just a little clinical
hypnotherapy practice I had.

00:55:41.560 --> 00:55:43.524 align:middle line:90%
And I was not a psychologist.

00:55:43.524 --> 00:55:45.190 align:middle line:84%
I just understood the
skill set and went

00:55:45.190 --> 00:55:46.510 align:middle line:84%
through that kind
of certification.

00:55:46.510 --> 00:55:47.510 align:middle line:90%
You can do it in months.

00:55:47.510 --> 00:55:49.220 align:middle line:90%
It's not a big deal right.

00:55:49.220 --> 00:55:52.157 align:middle line:84%
Psychologists will say,
oh, my god, don't do that.

00:55:52.157 --> 00:55:53.990 align:middle line:84%
But I always found it
was quite interesting.

00:55:53.990 --> 00:55:57.790 align:middle line:84%
I had some good success with
people doing this in the day.

00:55:57.790 --> 00:56:00.520 align:middle line:84%
And one thing I found
that was not taught--

00:56:00.520 --> 00:56:06.100 align:middle line:84%
and I can't say that my
instructor particularly

00:56:06.100 --> 00:56:07.810 align:middle line:84%
frowned on it, but
they didn't understand

00:56:07.810 --> 00:56:11.650 align:middle line:84%
it-- was that I started
doing silent sessions,

00:56:11.650 --> 00:56:14.650 align:middle line:84%
connecting with people in
their ideomotor response

00:56:14.650 --> 00:56:16.600 align:middle line:90%
silently, mind to mind.

00:56:16.600 --> 00:56:20.050 align:middle line:84%
And as long as there was
an environment of trust,

00:56:20.050 --> 00:56:21.100 align:middle line:90%
you could do this easily.

00:56:21.100 --> 00:56:26.320 align:middle line:84%
And had sometimes some really
profound transformations,

00:56:26.320 --> 00:56:28.520 align:middle line:84%
especially when I was
working with someone where

00:56:28.520 --> 00:56:30.150 align:middle line:90%
it was performance-oriented.

00:56:30.150 --> 00:56:32.530 align:middle line:84%
I would get an agreement
with them, mind to mind,

00:56:32.530 --> 00:56:35.260 align:middle line:84%
and they would just boom,
pop up in the competition

00:56:35.260 --> 00:56:38.090 align:middle line:84%
and not know what they had
done or been working on.

00:56:38.090 --> 00:56:40.330 align:middle line:84%
But I find that that's
actually a very powerful way

00:56:40.330 --> 00:56:44.890 align:middle line:84%
to work because it bypasses
all resistance-- the resistance

00:56:44.890 --> 00:56:47.270 align:middle line:84%
of all words, all
concepts, all ego.

00:56:47.270 --> 00:56:48.254 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing there--

00:56:48.254 --> 00:56:49.170 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: Holding space.

00:56:49.170 --> 00:56:51.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Except a pure holding
space for another person.

00:56:51.270 --> 00:56:52.270 align:middle line:90%
It was very effective.

00:56:52.270 --> 00:56:53.311 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: That's wonderful.

00:56:53.311 --> 00:56:55.360 align:middle line:84%
There's one other thing
that comes to mind since

00:56:55.360 --> 00:56:57.943 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about how to work
with trauma that we've learned

00:56:57.943 --> 00:57:01.090 align:middle line:84%
from Rosalyn and that many
healers are using today with

00:57:01.090 --> 00:57:03.010 align:middle line:84%
their work in with
PTSD patients,

00:57:03.010 --> 00:57:05.020 align:middle line:84%
and that is actually
rooted in Vedic tradition--

00:57:05.020 --> 00:57:06.644 align:middle line:84%
it's probably other
traditions as well,

00:57:06.644 --> 00:57:08.830 align:middle line:84%
I think Egyptian
traditions and others--

00:57:08.830 --> 00:57:10.720 align:middle line:90%
called unwinding.

00:57:10.720 --> 00:57:14.710 align:middle line:84%
And this is understood to really
help release patterns that

00:57:14.710 --> 00:57:16.190 align:middle line:90%
again are on the karmic level.

00:57:16.190 --> 00:57:19.600 align:middle line:84%
So what it might look like is,
for example, a patient laying

00:57:19.600 --> 00:57:21.400 align:middle line:84%
on the table-- not
always, but can

00:57:21.400 --> 00:57:24.010 align:middle line:84%
look like this, where you have
your hands around their head.

00:57:24.010 --> 00:57:26.590 align:middle line:90%
And again, you're holding space.

00:57:26.590 --> 00:57:29.020 align:middle line:84%
And their bodies start
to move a little bit.

00:57:29.020 --> 00:57:30.580 align:middle line:90%
Their head starts to move.

00:57:30.580 --> 00:57:34.030 align:middle line:84%
And you can feel the
pattern releasing.

00:57:34.030 --> 00:57:36.700 align:middle line:84%
There are meditations that one
can do, unwinding meditations,

00:57:36.700 --> 00:57:38.075 align:middle line:84%
that are just good
because we all

00:57:38.075 --> 00:57:40.580 align:middle line:84%
get wound up in our little
patterns and things like that.

00:57:40.580 --> 00:57:43.990 align:middle line:84%
So this is a really
easy self-care practice

00:57:43.990 --> 00:57:45.430 align:middle line:90%
where one sits in meditation.

00:57:45.430 --> 00:57:48.580 align:middle line:84%
And it allows the body
to move freely in the way

00:57:48.580 --> 00:57:51.140 align:middle line:84%
that it wants to release those
patterns that are winding us

00:57:51.140 --> 00:57:51.940 align:middle line:90%
up.

00:57:51.940 --> 00:57:52.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:57:52.210 --> 00:57:53.336 align:middle line:90%
So be specific.

00:57:53.336 --> 00:57:54.460 align:middle line:90%
Is that all there is to it?

00:57:54.460 --> 00:57:55.891 align:middle line:90%
You sit quietly.

00:57:55.891 --> 00:57:56.890 align:middle line:90%
You're feeling wound up.

00:57:56.890 --> 00:57:58.990 align:middle line:84%
You sit quietly,
and you just allow

00:57:58.990 --> 00:58:01.360 align:middle line:84%
the body, of its
own intelligence,

00:58:01.360 --> 00:58:04.296 align:middle line:84%
to begin moving you,
just subtle movement?

00:58:04.296 --> 00:58:05.170 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: I would add--

00:58:05.170 --> 00:58:06.560 align:middle line:84%
I always think this
is a good practice,

00:58:06.560 --> 00:58:09.280 align:middle line:84%
especially in this day and age
-- make sure you're grounded.

00:58:09.280 --> 00:58:11.715 align:middle line:90%
So sit down, stand up, whatever.

00:58:11.715 --> 00:58:12.515 align:middle line:10%
Sitting is easier.

00:58:12.515 --> 00:58:13.315 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Breathe.

00:58:13.315 --> 00:58:16.000 align:middle line:10%
>>JAIN: Breathe, feel
the base of your spine,

00:58:16.000 --> 00:58:19.330 align:middle line:10%
feel your feet on the ground,
feel your legs connect

00:58:19.330 --> 00:58:21.250 align:middle line:10%
with the earth, feel
supported by the earth,

00:58:21.250 --> 00:58:24.580 align:middle line:10%
support yourself, and send
support back down to the earth

00:58:24.580 --> 00:58:27.390 align:middle line:10%
so you really have that firm
connection with the earth.

00:58:27.390 --> 00:58:29.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then let
the movement just--

00:58:29.140 --> 00:58:30.880 align:middle line:84%
>>JAIN: And then let
the movement begin.

00:58:30.880 --> 00:58:33.580 align:middle line:84%
So that way you don't get dizzy
or feel a little lightheaded

00:58:33.580 --> 00:58:34.600 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

00:58:34.600 --> 00:58:35.860 align:middle line:90%
You're really grounded.

00:58:35.860 --> 00:58:37.660 align:middle line:84%
And this process
can be five minutes.

00:58:37.660 --> 00:58:40.330 align:middle line:90%
It can be 45 minutes.

00:58:40.330 --> 00:58:42.250 align:middle line:84%
I think Rosalyn and
Ken recommend doing it

00:58:42.250 --> 00:58:44.110 align:middle line:90%
about twice a week if you can.

00:58:44.110 --> 00:58:45.560 align:middle line:90%
I found it to be very helpful.

00:58:45.560 --> 00:58:46.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I've done
it just spontaneously

00:58:46.870 --> 00:58:48.200 align:middle line:90%
off and on throughout my life.

00:58:48.200 --> 00:58:49.720 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know exactly
what was going on,

00:58:49.720 --> 00:58:51.803 align:middle line:84%
except I assumed it was
working through something.

00:58:51.803 --> 00:58:54.340 align:middle line:84%
I find it very
natural and beautiful.

00:58:54.340 --> 00:58:56.750 align:middle line:84%
Give us maybe-- we just have
a couple of minutes left--

00:58:56.750 --> 00:59:01.240 align:middle line:84%
maybe one little Jain meditation
or a prayer, or something

00:59:01.240 --> 00:59:02.994 align:middle line:90%
universal that we can work with.

00:59:02.994 --> 00:59:04.160 align:middle line:90%
>>JAIN: I'd love to do that.

00:59:04.160 --> 00:59:05.190 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:59:05.190 --> 00:59:07.627 align:middle line:84%
So I'll share with you
a Jan universal prayer,

00:59:07.627 --> 00:59:09.460 align:middle line:84%
and I'll explain a
little bit of the meaning

00:59:09.460 --> 00:59:13.510 align:middle line:84%
before I say the words, which
of course are in Sanskrit.

00:59:13.510 --> 00:59:16.550 align:middle line:84%
So the prayer is a universal
prayer for everyone.

00:59:16.550 --> 00:59:19.230 align:middle line:84%
As I mentioned, Jainism doesn't
believe in a creator god.

00:59:19.230 --> 00:59:20.770 align:middle line:84%
This is really a
universal prayer

00:59:20.770 --> 00:59:23.320 align:middle line:84%
to all beings who have
attained enlightenment

00:59:23.320 --> 00:59:25.120 align:middle line:84%
or are teaching the
path of enlightenment

00:59:25.120 --> 00:59:27.400 align:middle line:90%
and giving reverence to them.

00:59:27.400 --> 00:59:28.740 align:middle line:90%
So the prayer starts--

00:59:28.740 --> 00:59:30.520 align:middle line:84%
I'll first say it,
and then if it's OK,

00:59:30.520 --> 00:59:33.040 align:middle line:84%
I'll just sing it, because
that's how we usually do it.

00:59:33.040 --> 00:59:36.910 align:middle line:84%
So the prayer is Namo
arihantanam which means I bow

00:59:36.910 --> 00:59:40.390 align:middle line:84%
to all the [NON-ENGLISH],, those
who have conquered themselves,

00:59:40.390 --> 00:59:44.160 align:middle line:84%
those who have stayed to teach
the way of enlightenment.

00:59:44.160 --> 00:59:46.060 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH].

00:59:46.060 --> 00:59:49.530 align:middle line:84%
I bow to all those who have
attained enlightenment.

00:59:49.530 --> 00:59:51.510 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH].

00:59:51.510 --> 00:59:54.390 align:middle line:84%
I bow to all heads of
congregations that are holding

00:59:54.390 --> 00:59:56.790 align:middle line:90%
space for this learning.

00:59:56.790 --> 00:59:59.530 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH].

00:59:59.530 --> 01:00:04.080 align:middle line:84%
I bow, again, to some of the
major monks and nuns that

01:00:04.080 --> 01:00:06.288 align:middle line:90%
are teaching the way.

01:00:06.288 --> 01:00:11.910 align:middle line:84%
[NON-ENGLISH] I bow to all
teachers of spirituality.

01:00:11.910 --> 01:00:14.090 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH].

01:00:14.090 --> 01:00:19.520 align:middle line:84%
By bowing to these five
beings, [NON-ENGLISH],,

01:00:19.520 --> 01:00:23.560 align:middle line:90%
may all darkness be removed.

01:00:23.560 --> 01:00:28.970 align:middle line:10%
[NON-ENGLISH] basically
means this is a very revered,

01:00:28.970 --> 01:00:31.020 align:middle line:10%
ancient prayer.

01:00:31.020 --> 01:00:33.102 align:middle line:10%
So we will sing it now,
or I'll sing it for you.

01:00:33.102 --> 01:00:34.560 align:middle line:10%
I sing this to my
kids every night.

01:00:34.560 --> 01:00:35.864 align:middle line:10%
You'll love it.

01:00:35.864 --> 01:00:38.696 align:middle line:90%
